            "title": "Word and Image in Russian History : Essays in Honor of Gary Marker",
            "abstract": [
                "Frontmatter -- Contents -- Acknowledgements -- List of Illustrations -- Introduction -- Tabula Gratulatoria -- A Biographical Essay: The Making of the Historian / Kaiser, Daniel H. -- From Publishing to Prokopovich: Gary Marker's Scholarly Contributions / Kivelson, Valerie A. -- Word -- Once Again on Whether Byzantine Law Was Applied to the Administration of the Law in Medieval Rus' / Zhivov, Viktor -- About Peter the Great's Ship Predestinatsiia / Salvo, Maria Di -- Eighteenth-Century Botanical Literature and the Origins of an Elite Russian Gardening Community / Ruane, Christine -- Catherine's Liberation of the Greeks: High-Minded Discourse and Everyday Realities / Smilianskaia, Elena -- A Proletarian Encyclop\u00e9die / Steila, Daniela -- Image -- The Parsuna of Gavrila Fetiev: Can a Picture Speak? / Kaiser, Daniel H. -- Tracking the Travels of Adam Olearius / Kollmann, Nancy S. -- Catherine the Great and the Art of Collecting: Acquiring the Paintings that Founded the Hermitage / Whittaker, Cynthia Hyla -- Rozanov's Peter / Dixon, Simon -- Gender -- The Question of Women in Power in the Eighteenth Century / Anisimov, E. V. -- Businesswomen in Eighteenth-Century Russian Provincial Towns / Kamenskii, Alexander -- Religion -- Dialogue and Conflict in the Ostroh Principality: The Year 1636 / Bercoff, Giovanna Brogi -- Connecting the Dots: Jewish Mysticism, Ritual Murder, and the Trial of Mendel Beilis / Weinberg, Robert -- Forms of Literacy -- Education and the East: The Omsk Asiatic School / Hartley, Janet M. -- What Should One Teach? A New Approach to Russian Childhood Education as Reflected in Manuscripts from the Second Half of the Seventeenth Century / Kosheleva, Ol'ga -- The Education of Parish Clergy in the Kyiv Eparchy in the 1770s / Iaremenko, Maksym -- Civil Society and Politics -- Civil Society and Politics / O'Meara, Patrick -- The Imperial Russian Noble Elite and Westernization: The Family Eizen-fon- Shvartsenberg / Bartlett, Roger -- \"Only the principle of public life and the full rights of citizenship\": The Russian Technical Society, the Public Sphere, and the Revolution of 1905 / Bradley, Joseph -- Publications of Gary Marker / Kaiser, Daniel H.",
                "Word and Image invokes and honors the scholarly contributions of Gary Marker. Twenty scholars from Russia, the United Kingdom, Italy, Ukraine and the United States examine some of the main themes of Marker's scholarship on Russia-literacy, education, and printing; gender and politics; the importance of visual sources for historical study; and the intersections of religious and political discourse in Imperial Russia. A biography of Marker, a survey of his scholarship, and a list of his publications complete the volume. Contributors: Valerie Kivelson, Giovanna Brogi (University of Milan), Christine Ruane (University of Tulsa), Elena Smilianskaia (Moscow), Daniela Steila (University of Turin), Nancy Kollmann (Stanford University), Daniel H. Kaiser (Grinnell College), Maria di Salvo (University of Milan), Cynthia Whittaker (City Univ. of New York), Simon Dixon (University of London), Evgenii Anisimov (St. Petersburg), Alexander Kamenskii (Higher School of Economics, Moscow), Janet Hartley (London School of Economics), Olga Kosheleva (Moscow State University), Maksim Yaremenko (Kyiv), Patrick O'Meara (University of Durham), Roger Bartlett (London), Joseph Bradley (University of Tulsa), Robert Weinberg (Swarthmore College)"
